## Proposed Changes — Phase by Phase

### Phase 1: Project Setup & ETL Pipeline (Month 1)

This phase establishes the foundation. Everything else depends on clean, loaded data.

---

#### [NEW] [requirements.txt](file:///c:/Users/21261/Desktop/dislog-pfe/requirements.txt)

Core dependencies:

```
pandas>=2.0
numpy>=1.24
scikit-learn>=1.3
xgboost>=2.0
matplotlib>=3.7
seaborn>=0.12
plotly>=5.15
mlxtend>=0.23          # For Apriori / association rules
sqlalchemy>=2.0
pyodbc>=5.0            # For SQL Server (or psycopg2 for PostgreSQL)
jupyter>=1.0
streamlit>=1.28        # For dashboard (optional if using Power BI)
scipy>=1.11
```

---

#### [NEW] [src/config.py](file:///c:/Users/21261/Desktop/dislog-pfe/src/config.py)

Central configuration:
- Database connection string
- File paths to raw CSVs
- Constants (encoding `cp1252` for ANSI files, date formats)
- Analysis reference date for RFM

---

#### [NEW] [src/etl/extract.py](file:///c:/Users/21261/Desktop/dislog-pfe/src/etl/extract.py)

- Read each CSV with proper encoding (`cp1252` for SalesLine, Invoice; `utf-8` for others)
- Handle large files with chunked reading (`chunksize` parameter in pandas)
- Log row counts and basic stats during extraction

---

#### [NEW] [src/etl/transform.py](file:///c:/Users/21261/Desktop/dislog-pfe/src/etl/transform.py)

- Clean column names (strip whitespace, lowercase)
- Cast types: `saleid` → `int64`, dates → `datetime`, amounts → `float64`
- Handle nulls: fill or drop based on business rules
- Remove duplicates
- Validate referential integrity (e.g., every `accountid` in SalesHeader exists in Customer)

---

#### [NEW] [src/etl/load.py](file:///c:/Users/21261/Desktop/dislog-pfe/src/etl/load.py)

- Create database tables using the schema
- Bulk insert cleaned data using SQLAlchemy + `to_sql()` with chunked inserts
- Verify row counts match between CSV and database

---

#### [NEW] [notebooks/01_data_profiling.ipynb](file:///c:/Users/21261/Desktop/dislog-pfe/notebooks/01_data_profiling.ipynb)

Initial data exploration notebook:
- Load each CSV and display shape, dtypes, head, describe
- Check for missing values, duplicates, outliers
- Visualize distributions of key fields (amounts, dates, quantities)
- Document data quality issues found

---

### Phase 2: EDA & Feature Engineering (Month 2)

---

#### [NEW] [notebooks/02_eda.ipynb](file:///c:/Users/21261/Desktop/dislog-pfe/notebooks/02_eda.ipynb)

Deep exploratory analysis:
- Sales trends over time (monthly/quarterly)
- Revenue distribution by region, sector, brand
- Customer purchase frequency distribution
- Top customers, top products, top sellers
- Correlation analysis between numerical fields

---

#### [NEW] [src/features/rfm.py](file:///c:/Users/21261/Desktop/dislog-pfe/src/features/rfm.py)

RFM Feature Engineering module:
- **Recency**: Days since last purchase (from reference date)
- **Frequency**: Total number of orders per customer
- **Monetary**: Total spend per customer
- RFM scoring (1-5 scale for each dimension)
- Composite RFM segment labels (e.g., "Champions", "At Risk", "Hibernating")

---

#### [NEW] [notebooks/03_rfm_analysis.ipynb](file:///c:/Users/21261/Desktop/dislog-pfe/notebooks/03_rfm_analysis.ipynb)

- Compute RFM scores for all customers
- Visualize RFM distributions (3D scatter, heatmaps)
- Segment customers using RFM rules
- Analyze segment sizes and revenue contribution

---

### Phase 3: ML Models — Segmentation & Churn (Month 3)

---

#### [NEW] [src/models/segmentation.py](file:///c:/Users/21261/Desktop/dislog-pfe/src/models/segmentation.py)

Clustering module:
- StandardScaler preprocessing
- K-Means with Elbow method and Silhouette score for optimal `k`
- DBSCAN as alternative for non-spherical clusters
- PCA for 2D/3D visualization of clusters
- Cluster profiling (mean RFM per cluster)

---

#### [NEW] [notebooks/04_segmentation.ipynb](file:///c:/Users/21261/Desktop/dislog-pfe/notebooks/04_segmentation.ipynb)

- Run segmentation pipeline
- Compare K-Means vs DBSCAN results
- Visualize clusters with PCA
- Business interpretation of each segment
- Recommend strategies per segment (e.g., "re-engage At Risk customers with discounts")

---

#### [NEW] [src/models/churn.py](file:///c:/Users/21261/Desktop/dislog-pfe/src/models/churn.py)

Churn prediction module:
- Define churn label (e.g., no purchase in last 90 days)
- Feature engineering for churn (recency, frequency, avg order value, days between orders)
- Train/test split (80/20, stratified)
- Models: Logistic Regression (baseline), Random Forest, XGBoost
- Evaluation: Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1, AUC-ROC
- Feature importance analysis
- SHAP values for model explainability (optional but impressive)

---

#### [NEW] [notebooks/05_churn_prediction.ipynb](file:///c:/Users/21261/Desktop/dislog-pfe/notebooks/05_churn_prediction.ipynb)

- Build and compare churn models
- Confusion matrix, ROC curve, precision-recall curve
- Feature importance plots
- Identify top at-risk customers

---

